HEADWORD: Botryoidal
<hw>Bot`ry*oid"al</hw>
<pr>(<?/)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <ets><?/</ets> cluster
of grapes + <ets>-oid</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having the form of a bunch of
grapes; like a cluster of grapes, as a mineral presenting an aggregation
of small spherical or spheroidal prominences; <as>as,
<ex>botryoidal</ex> hematite</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> botryose.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

